# =============================================================================
# NOTES FOR THE USER
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. This is a SKELETON. It will not build as-is. Split it into the modular
#    structure from architecture.md, fix all TODO markers, and remove the
#    block comments around the flake.nix and home-manager sections.
#
# 2. After first install, run `nixos-generate-config --root /mnt` and use
#    the generated hardware-configuration.nix. Do NOT hand-write it.
#
# 3. The `system.stateVersion` and `home.stateVersion` should match the
#    NixOS version at time of initial install. Never change these after.
#
# 4. Channel strategy:
#      - nixpkgs (stable 24.11) is the base for everything
#      - nixpkgs-unstable is available as `pkgs-unstable` for specific overrides
#      - Only use pkgs-unstable when stable has a concrete bug/version issue
#      - Document WHY in a comment next to every pkgs-unstable reference
#
# 5. Anti-creep rules:
#      - NEVER use `nix-env -i` -- always edit a .nix file
#      - Use `nix shell nixpkgs#pkg` for ephemeral one-off use
#      - Use devShells (flake.nix per project) for project toolchains
#      - Run `ngc` alias periodically (or rely on weekly auto-GC)
#      - Keep configurationLimit = 5 to keep boot menu clean
#
# 6. Build and test without switching:
#      sudo nixos-rebuild build --flake .#framework
#
# 7. Switch to a new configuration:
#      sudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake .#framework
#
# 8. Rollback:
#      sudo nixos-rebuild switch --rollback
#
# 9. Update packages:
#      nix flake update                        # Update all inputs
#      nix flake update nixpkgs                # Update only stable
#      nix flake update nixpkgs-unstable       # Update only unstable
#      sudo nixos-rebuild switch --flake .#framework
#
# 10. Search for packages:
#      nix search nixpkgs#<name>
#      Or visit https://search.nixos.org/packages
#
# 11. Unfree packages (VS Code, Chrome, Steam, Zoom, Citrix, Discord,
#     Obsidian, JetBrains, etc.) require `nixpkgs.config.allowUnfree = true`.
#
# 12. For packages NOT in nixpkgs (Betterbird, Speech Note):
#     Use Flatpak. Enable via `services.flatpak.enable = true` and
#     install with `flatpak install flathub <app-id>`.
#
# 13. Dual DE: Both KDE and GNOME are enabled. At SDDM login, pick your
#     session from the dropdown. GNOME Online Accounts replaces Insync
#     for Google Drive / OneDrive when in GNOME sessions.
#
